Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_tap_walls(25.10)                                      add_tap_walls(25.10)

Name
       add_tap_walls - Adds tap walls to the assigned left, right, top, and/or
       bottom side of a block

Syntax
       add_tap_walls

       [-help]

       [-bottom]

       -cell <cellName>

       [-layer <layer_name>]

       [-left]

       [-orientation {R0 MX MY R180}]

       [-pitch <distance>]

       [-prefix <prefix>]

       [-range <lx ux>|<ly uy>]

       [-right]

       [-top]

       [-y_flip_side {left right both}]

       Adds  tap walls to the assigned left, right, top, and/or bottom side of
       a block.

Parameters
       -bottom
              Specifies the add tap-wall cell on the bottom side.

       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the name of the cell to insert.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each add_tap_walls parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man add_tap_walls.

       -layer <layer_name>
              Specifies the layer name to check rule.

       -left  Specifies the add tap-wall cell on the left side.

       -orientation {R0 MX MY R180}
              Specifies orientation of the added tap-wall cells.

       -pitch <distance>
              Specifies  the  distance from the center of one tap-wall cell to
              the center of the following wall-tap cell.

       -prefix <prefix>
              Specifies the prefix of tap-wall cells to inserted.

       -range <lx ux>|<ly uy>
              Specifies the {lx, ux} or {ly uy} as the start or end  point  at
              the user given side.

       -right Specifies the add tap-wall cell on the right side.

       -top   Specifies the add tap-wall cell on the top side.

       -y_flip_side {left right both}
              Specifies the orientation of the added tap-wall cells.

              Defines  whether  flipping  tap walls located at certain side in
              the Y direction if site symmetry allows  it.  By  default,  both
              left  and  right side tap walls are R0 or MX. If -y_flip_side is
              set to left, the left side tap walls would be MY or R180. If  it
              is  set  to both, both left and right side tap walls would be MY
              or R180.

